cs.ET, cs.IT, cs.QU, cs.NI, cs.SY

This paper deals with the capacity region of a quantum switch serving a set of users, which involves the study of information theory, quantum information processing, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers quantum computing and communication. The paper also involves the modeling of randomized switching policies, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The study of entangled states and qubit decoherence suggests the category of cs.QU (Quantum Physics). The paper also presents analytical results for the performance of different policies, which involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms, and hence, the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely. Finally, the study of the switch's behavior and capacity region can be seen as a control problem, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
